What to Do Next?
How to Track Your Order?
Go to Your Orders
Identify the order that you want to track.
Select Track Package next to the selected order.
Select 'See all Updates'. The status of the order will have the details of the courier partner.
Important Notes

Multiple items: If your order includes multiple items, each item may have a separate delivery date and tracking information.
Seller-shipped items: Items shipped by sellers can be tracked only if the seller has shared order tracking information with Amazon. If you have chosen a traceable shipping method, you can also get the details.
Courier information: Find details about delivery partners on the Our Courier Partners
How to Identify the Delivery Partner?

Your order can be delivered by Amazon or a third-party courier.

Items delivered by Amazon have the following Amazon-delivered logo in the product description.



Seller-delivered products on Amazon have this message on the product detail page: "Sold by (seller name) and Ships from (seller name)".
If Your Package is Delayed.

Allow extra time for delivery. Packages usually arrive on or shortly after the estimated delivery date.

Amazon-shipped packages: Wait for one more day.
Third-party courier packages: Wait for five more days.
If Your Package Has In-Transit Issues.

Check your tracking status for specific messages and follow instructions based on what is mentioned.

If Tracking shows messages such as: "Problem occurred", "Returning to Seller", or "Undeliverable" order -

Verify your shipping address in Your Orders.
Check that you entered a complete address with:
Building name or number
Street number
Area or locality
Nearest landmark
City, town, or village
Correct pincode
For more information about why packages become undeliverable, go to Undeliverable Packages

If the Package is marked as "Delivered" but you haven't received it.

Contact us within seven days of the order being marked as delivered. Go to Find a Missing Package that Shows as Delivered for more information.

What to Do Next?
You can also refer to this additional information:

For Amazon-shipped orders: Visit our Shipping and Delivery Help page for details related to -
Delivery of your Shipment
Delivery Speeds and Charges
Rescheduling a Delivery, and
Undeliverable Packages.
For seller-shipped orders: Contact the seller directly through Your Orders.

Shipment is Late
Learn more about why your Amazon delivery is late and track the steps to avoid delayed delivery.


To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on top banner and use the drop down to select the language.

Most orders are delivered on time. However, occasionally orders may be delivered after the estimated delivery date. Here are some of the possible reasons for late delivery:

Incorrect address
Missing apartment, building, floor, or house number
Severe weather conditions
Product damaged during transit
Local or regional contingencies

For late shipments: Check Your Orders page. Check for attempted delivery note. Check messages. Check delivery location, and with household and neighbours. Contact courier partner


If your shipment is late, check the following:
Track your package and confirm the estimated delivery date in Your Orders. We update the information if there is a change in the estimated delivery date.
Confirm your shipping address in Your Orders. To avoid delivery problems, keep your address information up-to-date and add delivery instructions to Your Addresses.
Wait for 48 hours to allow for any unexpected delays. We typically notify customers if any delays in delivery occurs.
If there is no tracking update after 48 hours and you have not received a delivery notification, contact our Customer Service team for further assistance.
If delivery was attempted once and failed to deliver, we will attempt delivery again on the following day.
If you haven't received your order but tracking is labelled as delivered, go to Find a Missing Package That Shows As Delivered.
Note:
If your package shows as undeliverable, we will take care of the return and refund where applicable. When our delivery associates or courier partners are unable to deliver the item to the right recipient, packages are returned to us as undeliverable. Visit Undeliverable Packages Help page for details.
We can't expedite or reschedule to a day before the estimated delivery date.
The A-to-Z Guarantee protects you when you buy items sold and fulfilled by a third-party seller
 (these are items "Sold By - Seller Name" or "Shipped By - Seller Name"). It covers both the 
 timely delivery and condition of your items. To know more about A-to-Z Guarantee, go to the
  A-to-Z Guarantee Help page.


