Order shows as ‘Delivered’ but Not Received – Frequently Asked Questions
Guidance on reporting the order that shows delivered but not received. If your order shows as delivered but you have not received it, you can 'Raise a query' in the app.

To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on the top banner and use the drop down to select your language.

To know the status of your order, visit Your Orders and select the relevant order:

Your Orders
Possible Reasons (why the order shows as 'delivered')
If your order consisted of multiple items and only a few were delivered to you, it's possible that the other items in your order were dispatched in another shipment.

Your family members/ neighbors or reception might have collected the package on your behalf.

My order says 'delivered', but I didn't receive it. What should I do?
If your package is marked as delivered but you haven't received the package, we recommend using the self-serve option in your account to submit a query.

Note:
To help us take timely action, please report the issue within 7 days from the date of delivery.
Queries submitted after 7 days are not eligible for rescue.
Pay on Delivery orders are not eligible for rescue, please place a new order.
How can I report a package that says delivered, but not received?
To report a package that shows as delivered but hasn't been received, please follow these steps:

Go to Your Account and select Contact Us.
Choose the Chat with Us option.
Describe the issue as Package not received.
Select the item that is marked as Delivered.
Follow the on-screen instructions and you’ll be given the option to Raise a Query.
Review the summary of your issue and select Submit.
We will investigate the issue and keep you updated through your account.

What happens after I submit a query? How can I check the status?
Once your query is submitted, you’ll receive confirmation along with a date by which the issue will be resolved.

To check the status of your query at any time:
Go to Your Account and select Contact Us.
Choose the Chat with Us option.
Describe the issue as Package not received.
Select the item marked as delivered.
You will find an option to check the status of your query.
Below is an explanation for status update:

Status

Explanation

"Your Query is submitted successfully"

Your request has been submitted, and the delivery station has been notified.

"Your Query is under review"

The delivery team is actively investigating and attempting to locate your package.

"Your Resolution is ready"

The investigation is complete, and we now have the final update regarding your package. Please contact customer service for update.

Our Customer Support team will reach out to you during the investigation if any additional information is needed.

If you haven't received an update within 2 business days, please contact Customer Support for further assistance.

What if I don't have the option to raise a query in my account?
If the self-serve feature isn't available for your order, please contact Customer Support to raise a query manually.

Once submitted, please allow up to 2 days for updates.

What if my order was sold and shipped by a third-party seller?
If your item is fulfilled by a third-party seller:

Contact the seller through Your Orders.
Allow the seller for up to 3 business days to respond via email.
If you don't receive a response, you can file a claim under the A-to-Z Guarantee.
Undeliverable Packages
Read on to find out what you can do if your order has been marked "undeliverable" in your order tracking. In cases where the order has been marked undeliverable, Amazon will refund to your original payment method once we receive the item. Find out reasons why your order might be marked "undeliverable" here.


To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on top banner and use the drop down to select the language.

To track a package or check the status of your refund, go to

Your Orders
An order may be returned as undeliverable due to any of the following reasons:


Unavailability of recipient to accept the delivery, even after multiple attempts.
The shipment is detected to contain products with quality issues.
The address was incorrect or the pincode and area mentioned in the address does not match, or driver safety concerns due to presence of a dog. Visit Your Addresses to update your shipping addresses and delivery preferences. Customize instructions to include presence of dog.
Recipient refused delivery.
In rare cases, the address label became unreadable during shipping.
The package was damaged in transit.
Local and regional contingencies prevented the delivery of the item.
Severe weather conditions affected the delivery.
Customer could not be contacted over call and:
There was no safe location to deliver the package.
The security or mailroom personnel didn’t accept the package
Access codes was needed to enter automated doors

After Amazon receives the return item, it takes up to 5 working days for a credit card, debit card, or UPI-linked bank account refund. It takes up to 4 hours for an Amazon Pay balance refund.

What happens to undeliverable orders:
All undeliverable packages are returned to our fulfillment center within 13 days.
We cannot ship the orders again that have been returned to us.
Once we receive the package, your order will be cancelled and refund will be processed to original payment method. The refund timeline will depend upon the payment mode chosen by you. To know about refund timelines, refer to About Refunds Help page. You may also check Amazon.in Refund policy for more details.
Note:
Our courier partners cannot retrieve and deliver an undeliverable package, even if it is at a local courier station. You may cancel the order and place a new order if you still need the product
If the product was sold and shipped by a third-party seller (these are items "Sold By - Seller Name" or "Shipped By - Seller Name"), please contact the seller for undelivered packages.
Our A-to-Z Guarantee protects you against any issues related to products sold and shipped by third-party seller. It covers both timely delivery and condition of the items. Visit A-to-Z Guarantee Help page to learn more
Cancel Items and Orders
You can cancel items or orders by visiting the Your Orders section in Your Account.



To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on top banner and use the drop down to select the language.


Desktop cancellation: Select Your orders. Select Cancel items. Select the item's checkbox. Select Cancel selected items.


Want to cancel an item or order? Visit

Your Orders
To cancel orders before they are shipped:

Visit Your Orders.
Select the item you want to cancel and select Cancel items.
Provide reasons for cancellation (optional) and proceed.
To cancel orders that are already shipped:

Visit Your Orders.
Select the Request Cancellation option and proceed.
The items will be returned to Amazon for a refund (if the payment is already made).

Note: In case you are still contacted for delivery or do not see an option to cancel in Your Orders, please refuse to accept the order at the time of delivery.
For your cancelled orders, we will refund the amount (if the payment is already made) to the original payment method. To know about the refund timelines, refer to Amazon.in Refund Policy.

Note:
If your order is combined with other active orders from your account and is shipped as a single shipment (common tracking number), then cancelling one order/item would result in cancellation of all the other orders/items combined in the shipment.
If you have canceled an order partially, the refund of the partially cancelled order will be issued once other items in the order have been fulfilled.
For orders shipped directly by the seller, you can cancel from Your Orders within 30 minutes by selecting View order details and then selecting Cancel Item. After 30 minutes, and up until the time the order ships, you can request a cancellation from the seller. Your order will be cancelled by the seller and refund will be processed to your original payment method by the seller, if the payment was already made. Visit Seller Fulfilled Orders help page for more details. In case you are still contacted for delivery or do not see an option to cancel in Your Orders, please refuse to accept the order at the time of delivery.
How to Schedule a Return
Returning your order? Learn about Amazon's return policies, return process for products including electronic devices, and refund process including Pay on Delivery orders.

To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on top banner and use the drop down to select the language.


To schedule a return for an eligible order, go to

Your Orders
Table of Contents

How to return an item I have ordered?
Do I need to print any return documentation?
How long does it take to refund after the item has reached Amazon?
How to get a refund for a Pay on Delivery order?
How to return an electronic device?
1. How to return an item I have ordered?

Select Returns and Orders on the top menu bar.
Choose the item that you want to return.
Select Return / Replacement. Enter the reason for return and tell us more.
Select Continue.
Follow the on-screen instructions. Choose the preferred date from the available options.
For refunds, you can choose to receive the amount either as an Amazon Pay balance or directly to your bank account. To receive a refund to your bank account, please ensure your bank details are added. Visit the help page Manage Bank Account for Refunds to know more.
Refer to the below image for steps on creating a successful return pick-up:



Steps for return pick-up: maintain item in original condition, add MRP tag, and place return label on the package.

2. Do I need to print any return documentation?

No, you do not need to print any documents.

3. How long does it take to process a refund after the item has reached Amazon?

A refund request will be initiated for your order when the returned package is received by Amazon.

To check the status of your refund, select the relevant order and select View Return / Refund Status.

Your Orders

4. How to get a refund for a Pay on Delivery order?

You can choose a refund to Amazon Pay balance or through NEFT to Bank Account. For NEFT to Bank Account, you'll need to add a bank account for refund.

5. How to return an electronic device?

If your return electronic device stores any personal information, please ensure that you have removed all such personal information from the device prior to returning. Amazon shall not responsible for any misuse or usage of such information.

Return Pick-up Issues
Navigate Amazon return pickup issues with ease. Learn how to handle failed pickups, cancel returns, and reschedule your pickups.


To access in your preferred language, locate the country flag on top banner and use the drop down to select the language.

To access the status of your return pick-up request, go to

Your Returns


Ensure item's in original condition. Add MRP tag, manual, warranty, accessories. Add return label if required. Select Returns centre.

A return pick-up can fail due to any of the following reasons:

Customer not available during pick-up slot: In case you were not available, Delivery Agents will try up to three attempts to reschedule pick-up after calling and confirming with you. After three failed attempts, the pick-up will be cancelled.
Product verification failed: Delivery Agent will check the product during pick-up. If the verification fails, because the product is not in its original state (has been used, missing price tags etc.,) the delivery agent may cancel the pick-up.
Return pickup cancelled by Amazon: At times the pick-up may get cancelled or cannot be attempted due to operational reasons.
Area Inaccessible/Not Serviceable: Pickup could not be completed as the address is currently inaccessible or outside the serviceable area.
Incomplete Address: Pickup failed due to an incomplete or incorrect address provided.
Uninstallation/Packaging Issue: Pickup could not be completed as the item was not uninstalled or packaged as required.
If your return pick-up has failed - you can follow the steps below to start a new return pick-up request.

Before you place a new request, please ensure: The product is in original condition (with MRP/price tag intact) and you are available during the pick-up slot.

Go to Online Returns Center.
Select the item that you have scheduled for return.
If the return request was approved, select View Return/Refund Status.
Select Manage Return.
Note: After you select "Manage Return" you’ll have options to reschedule your pickup, make changes to your return or choose to no longer return the product.
On the following page, select Cancel Return.
Once the active return request is cancelled, you can create a new pick-up request in Online Returns Centre. To schedule a return, visit How to Schedule a Return help page.
If your order was not eligible for return pick-up and you have already shipped your item to be returned (using Self-Ship option), you will not be able to cancel your return.


























































































































































































































































